# Repo-root build context exclusions.
#
# Several services build with the repo root as their Docker context
# (mira-ingest, mira-pipeline, mira-bots/telegram — all use explicit COPY
# allow-lists). Without this file the whole monorepo (node_modules, .git, .next,
# build artifacts, screenshots) is sent to the Docker daemon as the context —
# gigabytes, and slow on the VPS. Everything below is excluded from EVERY
# root-context build; none of those builds COPY any of these paths.
#
# NOTE: this does NOT affect the mira-hub image (its build context is ./mira-hub,
# governed by mira-hub/.dockerignore, if any).

# Version control + CI
.git
.github
.gitignore

# Node / Next.js (no Python service copies these)
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/build

# Python caches / virtualenvs
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.venv
**/venv
**/.pytest_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.mypy_cache

# Local env + secrets (secrets come from Doppler at runtime, never the image)
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log

# Promotional / proof screenshots + PDFs at the repo root (not copied by any build)
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.pdf
